# Console Class

The console class in C# is 

#!markdown

## Console.Write()

This method writes text to the console. It does not create a new line.

#!csharp

Console.Write("Hello");
Console.Write("Hello");

#!markdown

## Console.WriteLine()

This method writes line of text to the console. It creates a new line.

#!csharp

Console.WriteLine("Hello");
Console.WriteLine("Hello");

#!csharp

Console.Write('H');

#!csharp

Console.WriteLine(500);

string message = "This is a message";
Console.WriteLine(message);

#!markdown

